E60206




  
                  Architecture Sustainable(永續建築) 
   
                  ■內文簡介
The consciousness to respect the  
environment is increasingly latent in our society. This volume presents a series  
of practical examples where we study the trends and solutions used
We have made a careful selection of 
projects, which have been designed using sustainable parameters. With a uniform 
analytical scheme and complete graphic information, we present projects that are 
adapted to climatic conditions of locations from Australia to India, with 
particular emphasis on Spanish experiences. Through the examples shown, we can 
see how architecture which incorporates bioclimatic criteria from the project 
phase can materialize into high quality, comfortable buildings.

 　



  
